[{"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "These ex-Apple employees are bringing AI to the desktop", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Conrad Kramer, Kim Beverett, and Ari Weinstein of Software Applications Incorporated.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/m33ogJtIgro4Tg3WS_D92hmH8Lw=/0x0:4639x3093/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72914643/Software_Inc_cofounders.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>From left to right: Conrad Kramer, Kim Beverett, and Ari Weinstein of Software Applications Incorporated.</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"rBvVMK\">AI chatbots like ChatGPT have, to date, been fairly impersonal, existing outside of the apps and data that we use every day. A new startup by three ex-Apple employees called Software Applications Incorporated hopes to change that.</p>\n<p id=\"uiNBj8\">The company\u2019s CEO, Ari Weinstein, is a repeat founder, having sold his last startup, the iOS automation app Workflow, to Apple in 2017 alongside co-founder and CTO Conrad Kramer. This time, the two have been joined by Kim Beverett, a 10-year Apple vet who was onstage at this year\u2019s WWDC an", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/29/23981802/software-applications-inc-workflow-shortcuts-apple-employees-startup", "date_published": "2023-11-29T23:05:45+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": false, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "The CEOs of Meta, X, TikTok, Snap, and Discord will testify before the US Senate on child safety", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A picture of Meta CEO Mark Zuckerberg in front of a stylized Meta logo.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/Y-kBM4uhonfuTdehOHNOsAXqY38=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72914550/VRG_Illo_STK169_L_Normand_MarkZuckerburg_Neutral.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Laura Normand / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"L6gClo\">Some of the biggest names in tech will testify before the US Senate on January 31st, 2024 during a hearing about online child exploitation. In a <a href=\"https://www.judiciary.senate.gov/press/releases/durbin-graham-announce-january-2024-hearing-with-five-big-tech-ceos-on-their-failure-to-protect-children-online\">Wednesday announcement</a>, the Senate Judiciary Committee said it will hear from Meta CEO Mark Zuckerberg, X (formerly Twitter) CEO Linda Yaccarino, TikTok CEO Shou Zi Chew, Snap CEO Evan Spiegel, and Discord CEO Jason Citron.</p>\n<p id=\"pX6miJ\">Senators Dick Durbin (D-IL) and Lindsey Graham ", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/29/23981662/meta-x-tiktok-ceos-testify-us-senate-child-exploitation", "date_published": "2023-11-29T22:41:57+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": false, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "Evernote is about to seriously limit its plan for free users", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Evernote\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/iGAYaRVsyppAvhuRlsRCZBcN2fM=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72914524/jbareham_190314_3294_0011_2.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo by James Bareham / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"izRLbj\">Evernote is going to limit new and existing free users to a maximum of just 50 notes and one notebook starting December 4th, the company announced <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com?id=66960X1514734&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fevernote.com%2Fblog%2Fevernote-free-note-limits&amp;referrer=theverge.com&amp;sref=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theverge.com%2F2023%2F11%2F29%2F23981683%2Fevernote-limit-free-plan-notebook\" rel=\"sponsored nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">in a blog post on Wednesday</a>. The change, which Evernote <a href=\"https://techcrunch.com/2023/11/27/evernote-pushes-users-to-upgrade-with-test-of-a-free-plan-limited-to-only-50-notes/\">had been testing</a>, means that f", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/29/23981683/evernote-limit-free-plan-notebook", "date_published": "2023-11-29T22:35:20+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": false, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "Windows 11 tests energy saver mode for both laptops and desktop PCs", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Illustration of Microsoft\u2019s Windows logo\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/jSXpVBPLFWTb_zni6iVaovPxhsg=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72914387/acastro_STK109_microsoft_02.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration by Alex Castro / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"rZ67hu\"><a href=\"https://blogs.windows.com/windows-insider/2023/11/29/announcing-windows-11-insider-preview-build-26002-canary-channel/\">Microsoft is adding</a> an energy saver mode for Windows 11 Insiders (Build 26002) that \u201cextends and enhances\u201d the existing battery saver option. The new mode doesn\u2019t apply to just laptops like battery saver does \u2014 you can also<strong> </strong>use energy saver on a desktop computer if you want to conserve electricity, too.</p>\n<p id=\"t73njs\">Aside from availability on both desktop devices and laptops (even when they\u2019re plugged in), energy saver works pretty much the same as battery saver mode. The new feature al", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/29/23981581/windows-11-energy-saver-mode-laptops-pcs", "date_published": "2023-11-29T21:50:27+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": false, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "Google\u2019s Nest cameras can now tell you when your garage door is left open", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/t1mFA5RVZbg5O2n1MioTYZ4oaeo=/43x0:1578x1023/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72914268/Screen_Shot_2023_11_29_at_2.31.07_PM.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption><em>A Google Nest Cam set up in a garage will soon be able to send an alert if the door is left open.</em> | Screenshot by Jennifer Pattison Tuohy / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"NQbT2B\">Google\u2019s adding a new garage door detection feature to its Nest security cameras that will alert you if your garage door has been left open. The company is also bringing the first-gen Google Nest Outdoor Cam to the Google Home app and finally allowing Nest Cam users to create custom clips in the Google Home app.</p>\n<p id=\"wqu4kd\">These new features are part of the <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2022/11/9/23449215/google-home-app-public-preview\">Google Home app\u2019s public preview</a> and are rolling out this week. Adina Roth, product manager of Google", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/29/23981277/google-nest-cam-garage-door-detection-nest-app-google-home", "date_published": "2023-11-29T21:25:35+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": false, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "Microsoft Paint\u2019s OpenAI-powered \u2018Cocreator\u2019 image generator is here", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A picture of a pixelated cat generated by Paint Cocreator based on a user\u2019s description.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/hTDqCh0SMYD53FIIlz6YDZN7aJc=/0x1:1830x1221/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72914187/Paint_Cocreator.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Why draw the pixel cat in MS Paint when Cocreator can just make it for you?</em> | Image: Microsoft</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"anMpcf\">Microsoft is officially launching its Cocreator image-generating AI feature within the Paint app for Windows 11. The new integrated text-to-image generator, powered by OpenAI\u2019s <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/9/20/23881241/openai-dalle-third-version-generative-ai\">DALL-E 3</a> model, was previously <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/9/27/23892900/microsoft-dall-e-windows-11-paint-cocreator\">available only to Windows Insiders</a>. As <a href=\"https://www.windowscentral.com/software-apps/microsoft-paint-adds-dall-e-3-ai-in-windows-1", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/29/23981310/microsoft-ms-paint-cocreator-openai-ai-dall-e-3-text-to-image-generator-available", "date_published": "2023-11-29T21:02:35+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": false, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "Google agrees to pay publishers in Canada and drops plans for blocking news", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"An illustration of the Google logo.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/oeJJRDMNepLLwnw-qNDRLekXHYc=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72914168/STK093_Google_02.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration: The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"aTvXaT\">Google announced today that it won\u2019t <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/6/29/23778820/google-search-news-discover-canada-links\">pull links to Canadian news outlets after all</a>, thanks to an agreement with the government of Canada over the contentious Online News Act or Bill C-18. Google and Alphabet president of global affairs Kent Walker <a href=\"https://blog.google/intl/en-ca/company-news/outreach-initiatives/an-update-on-canadas-bill-c-18-and-our-search-and-news-products/\">published a statement</a> saying that \u201cfollowing extensive discussions, we are pleased that the Government of Canada has committed to addressing our core issues with Bill C-18,\u201d a rule designe", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/29/23981515/google-canadian-government-online-news-act-link-tax-agreement", "date_published": "2023-11-29T20:58:47+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": false, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "Apple and Spotify have revealed their top podcasts of 2023. Here is what they do \u2014 and don\u2019t \u2014 tell us.", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Illustration of a series of blue microphones on a teal background.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/zqMaEfy1t5NP1Rtf5FZie85K5T0=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72914056/VRG_Illo_STK427_K_Radtke_Getty_Mics.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration by Kristen Radtke / The Verge; Getty Images</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"hUDBQF\"><em>This is </em>Hot Pod<em>, </em>The Verge\u2019<em>s newsletter about podcasting and the audio industry. Sign up </em><a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/pages/hot-pod-podcast-audio-newsletter\"><em>here</em></a><em> for more.</em></p>\n<hr class=\"p-entry-hr\" id=\"lBqZy7\" />\n<p id=\"Ymod1U\">It\u2019s that time of year again, when all your friends share their <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/29/23980024/spotify-wrapped-2023-sound-town\">Spotify Wrapped</a> and you (read: me) reply with your boring <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/28/23979319/apple-music-replay-2023-spotify-wrapped\">Appl", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/29/23981468/apple-replay-spotify-wrapped-podcasts-rogan-crime-junkie-alex-cooper", "date_published": "2023-11-29T20:30:00+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": false, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "How to find your forgotten Gmail accounts", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Gmail icon against a background of small illustrations.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/N2n1646QEkbg06jj_7NWIqb0U5E=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72471439/HT011_gmail_00011.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration by Samar Haddad / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"YybQ39\">Last May, Google announced it was planning to <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/5/16/23725438/google-gmail-deleting-inactive-accounts\">delete any accounts that hadn\u2019t been used in two years</a> (with <a href=\"https://support.google.com/accounts/answer/12418290?visit_id=21689863370369-8660967798970125835&amp;p=inactive_account_policy_email&amp;rd=1\">a few exceptions</a>, such as accounts that have YouTube videos). And sure enough, about two months after that, I got an email from Google warning me that accounts that have not been accessed for two years will indeed be eligible for deletion starting on December 1st, 2023.</p>\n<p id=", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/23801642/gmail-accounts-lost-forgotten-recovery-how-to", "date_published": "2023-11-29T20:28:22+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": false, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "The best Bluetooth trackers for finding your stuff", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"The Chipolo Card spot and Tile Slim next to a keyring with an AirTag.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/aGWKtAmBktwRL-yR01QeGypcqEI=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72403263/vsong_220323_5100_0005.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Bluetooth trackers come in all shapes and sizes.</em> | Photo by Victoria Song / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n\n  \t\t <p>For those of us who don\u2019t ever seem to know where our keys, wallets, and remote controls have gone.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/23769840/best-bluetooth-trackers\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/23769840/best-bluetooth-trackers", "date_published": "2023-11-29T20:03:56+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": false, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "Tens of billions of dollars of IRA funding will now be earmarked for environmental justice", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Joe Biden stands at a podium in front of the White House with people standing behind him.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/Pe4zJdKBn3yR8LzDBXdTnsmlByw=/0x1:5744x3830/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72913975/1423446636.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>WASHINGTON, DC - SEPTEMBER 13, 2022: (L-R) U.S. Second Gentleman Doug Emhoff, U.S. First Lady Jill Biden U.S. President Joe Biden, U.S. Vice President Kamala Harris, U.S. Speaker of the House Nancy Pelosi (D-CA) and Senate Majority Leader Chuck Schumer (D-NY), stand onstage after the conclusion of an event celebrating the passage of the Inflation Reduction Act.</em> | Photo by Anna Moneymaker/Getty Images</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"OYSPUJ\">As money starts to roll out for the US\u2019s landmark clean energy and climate bill, a big chunk of the benefits will now be officially set aside for disadvantaged communities.</p>\n<p id=\"UOuaKn\">Programs totaling $118 billion in federal funding ", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/29/23981137/biden-ira-inflation-reduction-act-programs-justice40-initiative-exclusive", "date_published": "2023-11-29T20:00:00+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": false, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "Mailchimp is shutting down TinyLetter", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"An iPhone showing an email.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/KXdfp-_8rnccVskhJUEC0blbHvc=/0x0:1500x1000/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72913831/TinyLetter_Email_Device.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>This is an official press screenshot from TinyLetter. Throwback!</em> | Image: TinyLetter</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"Fl7rsd\">Mailchimp is shutting TinyLetter, a service that I loved that let individuals easily write and publish simple but nice-looking email newsletters. The service will be discontinued on February 29th, 2024, according to a message I see when logged into my TinyLetter account.</p>\n<p id=\"PyxCjU\">A user on X (formerly Twitter) shared a screenshot of what looks to be a message from Mailchimp that provides some additional context about the shutdown. Since Mailchimp acquired TinyLetter <a href=\"https://allthingsd.com/20110831/exclusive-mailchimp-buys-phil-kaplans-tiny-start-up-tinyletter/\">in 2011</a>, \u201cour busin", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/29/23981363/mailchimp-shutting-down-tinyletter", "date_published": "2023-11-29T19:24:37+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": false, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "How to scan your documents to PDFs using Google Drive", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Hand holding phone with Google logo against pink background with round blue illustrations.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/cjYa5G6SJpKTn4Qa3IjIkEIad7I=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72913478/HT012_google_0001.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration: Samar Haddad / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"Xq2zGt\">Google Drive users on Android have had the ability to scan documents and save them as PDFs for a while now. However, recently <a href=\"https://workspaceupdates.googleblog.com/2023/11/updates-to-google-drive-scanner-on-android-and-ios.html\">Google has upgraded that feature</a> for Android users, adding automatic captures, among other upgrades, and is also <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/29/23980739/google-drive-document-scanner-ios-android\">rolling out the feature for iOS users</a>. </p>\n<div class=\"c-float-left c-float-hang\"><aside id=\"Gq3xpF\"><div></div></aside></div>\n<p id=\"7Gt2Ua\">As soon", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/23980825/google-drive-pdf-scan-android-ios-how-to", "date_published": "2023-11-29T17:59:04+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": false, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "Amazon joins AI image creation fray with new model", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"AWS re:Invent 2023\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/_PIy-QPlku5py10B0H5APbZQaXI=/6x0:5928x3948/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72913331/1808364407.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo by Noah Berger / Getty Images for Amazon Web Services</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"kDHAXH\">Amazon is joining the AI image generation fray with the release of its Titan text-to-image AI model. Announced during the AWS re:Invent conference, Titan Image Generator can create \u201crealistic, studio-quality images\u201d and is supposed to have built-in guardrails against toxicity and bias. Titan isn\u2019t a standalone app or website but a tool that developers can build on to make their own image generators powered by the model; to use it, developers will need access to Amazon Bedrock.</p>\n<p id=\"knGAsj\">Swami Sivasubramanian, AWS vice president of database, analytics, and machine learning, previewed Titan Image Generator during his keynote, pointing to the model\u2019s a", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/29/23980697/amazon-ai-image-model-watermark-copyright", "date_published": "2023-11-29T17:25:11+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": false, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "Netflix gets its biggest games yet with GTA trilogy in December", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Graphic depicting three women from the Grand Theft Auto trilogy with the text \u201cGrand Theft Auto The Trilogy Definitive Edition\u201d\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/L4HqIe8M9xM-BEZkXu0Vlw8wTzw=/150x0:1770x1080/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72913258/gtanetflix.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Netflix</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"HiVYZk\">Netflix is adding the <em>Grand Theft Auto: The Trilogy \u2014 The Definitive Edition</em> to its ever expanding, ever impressive roster of games just in time for the holiday need-a-20-minute-break-from-the-family season.</p>\n<p id=\"faF7f1\"><em>Grand Theft Auto: The Trilogy \u2014 The Definitive Edition </em>(which we\u2019re going to call it the GTA Trilogy for simplicity\u2019s sake) is a remaster of <em>GTA III</em>, <em>GTA: Vice City</em>, and <em>GTA: San Andreas</em>. Players can pre-register for the game starting November 30th. It will be available both in the Netflix mobile app and offered separately to ", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/29/23981068/netflix-gta-trilogy-definitive-edition-mobile-release-date", "date_published": "2023-11-29T17:02:01+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": false, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "The Xbox app has a new compact mode for Windows handhelds", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"An Asus ROG Ally handheld running the Xbox app\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/orui924EYNtHfss8uN8Snpif9nw=/9x0:2552x1695/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72913185/rogallyxboxapp_twarren.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Here\u2019s a photo of compact mode on a ROG Ally.</em> | Photo by Tom Warren / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"GOqLb3\">Microsoft\u2019s new \u201ccompact mode\u201d that makes the Xbox PC app a little easier to use on handheld gaming PCs is now available. The company had <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/10/28/23936030/microsoft-xbox-app-windows-handheld-portable-rog-ally\">been testing the compact mode</a>, but thanks to an update to the Xbox PC app, you can now try it for yourself, <a href=\"https://news.xbox.com/en-us/2023/11/29/xbox-november-update-coming-soon/\">according to an Xbox Wire blog post</a>.</p>\n<p id=\"IcCEVk\">The big change for compact mode is that the sidebar collapses down into icons, meaning that the", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/29/23981086/xbox-app-compact-mode-windows-handhelds", "date_published": "2023-11-29T16:50:34+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": false, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "It\u2019s not just electricity \u2014 Bitcoin mines burn through a lot of water, too", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Wires stick out of specialized computers for Bitcoin mining glowing with green light\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/gNCDpeyU3KhkcgksRUeVjCAHnHg=/0x0:4000x2667/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72912926/1184520932.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Lights illuminate application-specific integrated circuit (ASIC) devices used for Bitcoin mining. | Andrey Rudakov/Bloomberg via Getty Images</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"9bb7lr\">Bitcoin mines aren\u2019t just energy-hungry, it turns out they\u2019re thirsty, too. The water consumption tied to a single Bitcoin transaction, on average, could be enough to fill a small backyard pool, according to a new analysis. Bitcoin mines are essentially big data centers, which have become notorious for how much electricity and water they use. </p>\n<p id=\"Fs6VPy\">Bitcoin\u2019s water footprint is growing, according to the analysis published today in a commentary in the journal <a href=\"https://www.cell.com/cell-reports", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/29/23979858/bitcoin-mine-cryptocurrency-water-use-analysis-energy", "date_published": "2023-11-29T16:00:00+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": false, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "Beyond Good & Evil is getting a 20th anniversary edition", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A screenshot from the video game Beyond Good &amp;amp; Evil.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/iBZXibAI8T1l3q6pW6k2WoriRKw=/0x34:800x567/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72912876/0000004058.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Ubisoft</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"tPYZPB\">A cult classic is getting a makeover next year. Ubisoft announced today that it\u2019s working on a 20th anniversary rerelease of <em>Beyond Good &amp; Evil </em>that\u2019s expected to launch in early 2024. The news comes after details of the release were <a href=\"https://www.ign.com/articles/beyond-good-evil-20th-anniversary-edition-pops-up-on-xbox-store\">posted early to the Xbox store</a>; not only that but Ubisoft also accidentally <a href=\"https://twitter.com/bgegame/status/1729872106123649325\">uploaded an unfinished version of the game to Ubisoft Plus</a>. \u201cThis version is not indicative of the final game,\u201d the company says.</p>\n<p id=\"efzXu4\">As for what the annive", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/29/23980960/beyond-good-and-evil-20th-anniversary-edition-2024", "date_published": "2023-11-29T15:46:58+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": false, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "DealBook Summit 2023: Elon Musk, Bob Iger, and more", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"New York Times DealBook Summit Held In New York City\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/bCm1lgeD2KoYTUtTBSp8-zSPsTg=/0x0:7324x4883/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72912856/1445788868.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>New York Times <em>CEO Meredith Kopit Levien in 2022.</em> | Photo by Michael M. Santiago / Getty Images</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p>We\u2019re reporting live from DealBook Summit 2023, where leaders in tech, media, and policy are sitting for interviews.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/29/23980877/new-york-times-dealbook-summit-elon-musk-bob-iger-david-zaslav\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/29/23980877/new-york-times-dealbook-summit-elon-musk-bob-iger-david-zaslav", "date_published": "2023-11-29T15:40:00+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": false, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "Sonos\u2019 original Move speaker is up to $160 off as a refurb", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A photo of the Sonos Move speaker.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/QsGuKelL7ZlGPlT1Pj6Ubk4MShY=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72912838/dseifert_190915_3647_0009.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>The Move makes a great indoor or outdoor speaker you can take all around the house.</em> | Photo by Dan Seifert / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"21guqR\">The sun may be setting on availability for the original <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2019/9/18/20871409/sonos-move-wireless-bluetooth-speaker-review-alexa-google-assistant-wifi-price-specs-sound-quality\"><strong>Sonos Move</strong></a> portable smart speaker. The newer <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/23877274/sonos-move-2-review\">Move 2</a> is in the process of replacing it, but that means there are some good deals to be had on the first-gen model before its gone. Sonos is selling the Move for <a href=\"https://www.anrdoezrs.net/links/8532386/type/dlg/sid", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/29/23980847/sonos-move-smart-speaker-nomad-magsafe-3in1-charger-deal-sale", "date_published": "2023-11-29T15:31:04+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": false, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "How to find your 2023 Spotify Wrapped", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Spotify logo against an illustrated background with round circle representing audio stuff.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/YqpCexEpkErq8KrcFScjMq2v2gw=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72912812/Audio_Spotify_HT008.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Samar Haddad / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"xLJUge\">One of the more popular end-of-year items is <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2022/11/30/23484880/spotify-wrapped-2022-music-personality-bad-bunny-harry-styles-joe-rogan\">Spotify Wrapped</a>, where the music service puts together a roundup of everything you listened to that year in various statistical formats, wrapped up (well, that\u2019s what it\u2019s called, right?) in bright, fun graphics. You can see what music categories you followed, get a playlist of your top 100 songs, see where you stand compared to others, and find out what your listening personality is. </p>\n<div class=\"c-float-left c-float-hang\"><asid", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/23980858/spotify-wrapped-2023-how-to", "date_published": "2023-11-29T15:28:39+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": false, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "The Pok\u00e9mon Horizons English dub finally hits Netflix in February", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/_f2Bi8MKyD2v51r6VPXg2K77MwM=/233x0:2648x1610/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72912801/Screen_Shot_2023_11_29_at_9.29.30_AM.0.png\" />\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"VjwV0W\">It\u2019s been about a year since <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2022/11/11/23451915/pokemon-ash-ketchum-ultimate-journeys-champion\">Ash Ketchum finally did the thing</a>, and the <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2022/12/16/23511362/new-pokemon-animated-series-scarlet-violet\">mainline <em>Pok\u00e9mon </em>anime sent him on his merry way</a> to make room for<a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/3/3/23623659/pokemon-scarlet-violet-anime-trailer\"> two new young protagonists</a> to take over the long-running series. Though <em>Pok\u00e9mon Horizons </em>has already been airing in Japan for a while now, it <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/23802206/pokemon-horizons-san-diego-comic-con-trailer\">hasn\u2019t been clear</a> when the show\u2019s English dub would debu", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/29/23980926/pokemon-horizons-netflix-premiere-date", "date_published": "2023-11-29T15:19:33+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": false, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "GM wants you to know that it\u2019s also unhappy with the slow pace of its EV business", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"GM CEO Mary Barra\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/C9TtDk9CtsCeQ_35on716XcEogI=/0x2:5000x3335/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72912664/1248230394.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Getty</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"4JP2me\">General Motors is dealing with a lot right now: <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/23934889/electric-vehicle-ev-transition-sales-delays-politics\">a slowing EV business</a>, <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/10/24/23930143/gm-delay-ev-chevy-equinox-silverado-sierra-q3-earnings\">delays in battery manufacturing</a>, <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/20/23969039/gm-cruise-kyle-vogt-ceo-resign-driverless-bet\">a safety crisis with its robotaxi unit</a>, Cruise, and <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/10/30/23938368/gm-uaw-tentative-deal-strike-autoworker-ev\">financial headwinds from the monthslong autoworker strike</a>. On top of it all, its stock price is still struggling to get back to where it", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/29/23980841/gm-mary-barra-ev-ultium-delay-cruise-cost-slash", "date_published": "2023-11-29T14:50:44+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": false, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "Spotify Wrapped 2023 is so popular, it\u2019s crashing", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"An illustration of the Spotify app logo\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/BGBU0o4T6pRBHFW9Ha7v6_HEmnk=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72912603/STK088_VRG_Illo_N_Barclay_2_spotify.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration by Nick Barclay / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"5tiCEl\">Spotify Wrapped, the yearly roundup that offers insight into your listening habits, started having issues shortly after its launch. While Spotify is <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/29/23980024/spotify-wrapped-2023-sound-town\">offering Wrapped on the web for the first time</a>, the experience isn\u2019t loading for some users.</p>\n<p id=\"2P0s3T\">Instead of landing on a login page when heading to <a href=\"https://www.spotify.com/us/wrapped/\">Spotify.com/wrapped</a>, some users (including myself and several others at <em>The Verge</em>) are seeing a blank webpage that says \u201c500 Internal Server Error.\u201d There are also <a href=\"http", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/29/23980891/spotify-wrapped-2023-500-error-outage-crashing", "date_published": "2023-11-29T14:30:33+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": false, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "DoorDash and Best Buy team up for on-demand tech deliveries", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"DoorDash\u2019s logo on a black and red background\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/2FARk9YrhsT_BRwC5Z4fnp9O_dM=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72912418/acastro_STK073_03.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration by Alex Castro / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"edahEF\">DoorDash is partnering with Best Buy to <a href=\"https://about.doordash.com/en-us/news/doordash-partners-with-best-buy\">offer customers on-demand delivery for tech products</a> like headphones, game controllers, tablets, and more. Going live today, users can find Best Buy in the DoorDash marketplace, alongside <a href=\"https://ir.doordash.com/news/news-details/2023/DoorDash-Announces-New-Retail-Partnerships-and-Shopping-Features-to-Help-Consumers-Get-What-They-Need-Now/default.aspx\">other non-restaurant businesses</a> like Lush, Victoria\u2019s Secret, and Party City. </p>\n<p id=\"Vme8pp\">Best Buy, which already has a <a href=\"https://www.theverge.co", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/29/23980078/doordash-best-buy-delivery-partnership", "date_published": "2023-11-29T14:00:00+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": false, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "HTC\u2019s Vive Ultimate Trackers are a sleeker way to keep tabs on your VR limbs and other objects", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/8HOBP1HMP1KPXVEx8xy-U2mRsEc=/0x0:2400x1600/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72912369/VIVE_Ultimate_Tracker_sports_training_rezzil_skillshot.0.jpg\" />\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"gmfqgd\">HTC\u2019s <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com?id=66960X1514734&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.vive.com%2Fus%2Faccessory%2Fvive-ultimate-tracker%2F&amp;referrer=theverge.com&amp;sref=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theverge.com%2F2023%2F11%2F29%2F23980817%2Fhtc-vive-ultimate-tracker-object-limb-tracking-vr-xr-elite\" rel=\"sponsored nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Vive Ultimate Tracker</a> is a new VR peripheral that\u2019s designed to track body parts like your feet or any other object you want to strap it to, the <a href=\"https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/htc-vive-announces-vive-ultimate-tracker-for-all-in-one-xr-headsets-and-pc-vr-streaming-301999898.html\">company has announced</a>. First <a href=\"https://www.roadtovr.com/htc-vive", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/29/23980817/htc-vive-ultimate-tracker-object-limb-tracking-vr-xr-elite", "date_published": "2023-11-29T13:36:51+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": false, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "Spotify Wrapped 2023 assigns you a \u2018sound town\u2019 based on your music taste", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"An image showing screenshots of Spotify Wrapped matching a user to a city\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/8x4KcYvyb0nQVEgmQznxWKzxM8Q=/300x0:3540x2160/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72912256/Sound_Town.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Spotify</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"JAKT05\">This year\u2019s <a href=\"https://www.spotify.com/us/wrapped/\">Spotify Wrapped</a> roundup is live. As was the case with previous years, it features a bundle of shareable stats that break down the most-listened artists, songs, and podcasts for 574 million users. But there <a href=\"https://newsroom.spotify.com/2023-11-29/wrapped-user-experience-2023/\">are also some surprises</a>, too, including a new system that assigns you a city based on your listening habits.</p>\n<p id=\"WHFeaN\">Although Spotify Wrapped largely features the same basic listening stats every year, it seems to always find fun new ways to serve them up. That element of fun is still missi", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/29/23980024/spotify-wrapped-2023-sound-town", "date_published": "2023-11-29T13:00:00+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": false, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "The Cybertruck made a mark but missed its moment", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Photo illustration of a Tesla Cybertruck.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/DgRJjefvyc8c0ykQAym-qJ8KOtY=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72912235/236937_Cybertruck_CVirginia.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>The Verge / Photo by Bloomberg, Getty Images</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n\n  \t\t <p>The long-delayed electric truck has finally arrived \u2014 sort of. Ten trucks are slated for delivery, but Tesla\u2019s problems extend far beyond\u00a0this first batch. </p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/29/23979850/tesla-cybertruck-delivery-design-production-problems-delay\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/29/23979850/tesla-cybertruck-delivery-design-production-problems-delay", "date_published": "2023-11-29T13:00:00+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": false, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "Robert De Niro accuses Apple of censoring awards speech", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"The 2023 Gotham Awards At Cipriani Wall Street On November 27, 2023 In New York City\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/U_Qoh1aQKBy4BrvstE_JhXiZ4vM=/0x817:2495x2480/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72912125/1817716612.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Robert De Niro, appearing onstage at the 2023 Gotham Awards in New York.</em> | Photo by Dimitrios Kambouris/Getty Images for The Gotham Film &amp; Media Institute</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"R7GWT5\">Robert De Niro slammed Apple and the Gotham Film &amp; Media Institute this week after claiming his speech for the Gotham Awards had been censored \u2014 allegedly by an Apple employee just minutes before the show started, according to <a href=\"https://variety.com/2023/film/news/robert-de-niro-apple-censors-trump-criticism-gotham-speech-1235810832/\"><em>Variety\u2019s</em> sources</a> \u2014 to remove criticisms about Donald Trump and the entertainment industry. </p>\n<p id=\"UYjlI0\">The actor appeared", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/29/23980781/robert-de-niro-apple-censoring-gotham-awards-speech-donald-trump", "date_published": "2023-11-29T12:09:16+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": false, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "Google beefs up Drive\u2019s document scanning feature and brings it to iPhone", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"An image showing the Google Drive logo on a blue background\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/dGTjUBxpQSyznIXjka_uQVJ5n3o=/0x0:3000x2000/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72911869/acastro_STK459_01.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration by Alex Castro / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"NaWs6c\">Google Drive users on iOS are getting a new scanning feature that lets them quickly photograph documents and add them to their libraries, the <a href=\"https://workspaceupdates.googleblog.com/2023/11/updates-to-google-drive-scanner-on-android-and-ios.html\">search giant has announced</a>. The feature has been <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2013/5/22/4355932/google-updates-drive-for-android-with-card-interface-scan-option\">available for Android for over a decade</a>, but until now iPhone and iPad users <a href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20230608035055/https://support.google.com/drive/answer/3145835?co=GENIE.Platform%3DiOS&amp;oc", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/29/23980739/google-drive-document-scanner-ios-android", "date_published": "2023-11-29T09:47:33+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": false, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "London\u2019s famed black cabs will be listed on Uber\u2019s app in big win for the ridehail company", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Bond Street In London\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/GCWAgJ6Q3s-YycR-oyFvVK8v88w=/0x0:5123x3415/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72911177/1735049082.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo by Mike Kemp / In Pictures via Getty Images</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"k2LS4A\">Uber notched another win in its <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/9/26/23888950/uber-taxi-driver-referral-third-party-los-angeles\">effort to win over the beleaguered taxi industry</a>, announcing a plan to start listing London\u2019s famed black cabbies in its app. </p>\n<p id=\"kVsOkb\">The service won\u2019t roll out until early 2024, but some London cabbies have already begun to sign up. Uber says all 15,000 of London\u2019s cab drivers \u201cwill now have the opportunity\u201d to sign up for Uber trip referrals. The company recently brokered deals with taxi fleet owners in New York City, Paris, Rome, and Los Angeles to list drivers in its app. </p>\n<p id=\"xIsCyk\">Next to New York\u2019s y", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/28/23979409/uber-london-black-cab-app-referrals-taxi-ltda", "date_published": "2023-11-29T00:00:00+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": false, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}]